  "prompt": "How does GiftCardMall.com make money?",
  "response": "GiftCardMall.com makes money through several revenue streams:\n\n1. Sales markup on gift cards\n- They sell gift cards at prices slightly higher than their face value\n- Earn a profit margin on each gift card sold\n\n2. Fees\n- Activation fees for gift cards\n- Service or processing fees\n- Shipping and handling charges\n\n3. Commissions from partner retailers\n- Earn a percentage when selling gift cards from various brands\n- Receive commissions for facilitating gift card transactions\n\n4. Bulk gift card sales\n- Offer discounts for corporate and bulk purchases\n- Generate revenue from large-volume sales\n\n5. Additional services\n- Personalized gift card design and customization\n- Gift card exchange or trade-in programs\n- Potential affiliate marketing partnerships\n\nThese multiple revenue sources allow GiftCardMall.com to generate income while providing a convenient platform for consumers to purchase and manage gift cards.",
